The '''Nhoras''' were a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]] that had been enemies of their neighbors the [[Clatear]] since around [[580 BBY]]. They both lived in a sector perhaps near [[Cilpar]]. Five generations of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] had unsuccessfully tried to resolve their vendetta.

When the Clatear came under [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] occupation, the Nhoras enjoyed the benefits of being ignored by the Empire as well as the Clatear. Unfortunately for the Nhoras, when the Empire pulled out, the Clatear found themselves with a well-armed military force. During the [[Caamas Document]] crisis, with the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] apparently either unwilling or unable to interfere with local conflicts, the Clatear-Nhoras conflict began to heat up once more. The Nhoras hired [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]], such as the [[Dhashaan Shield]], the retired [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] [[Dharus]], and possibly the [[Soskin Guard]], to help even the odds.

